name: Northern lights
summary: Multiple news outlets are reporting that the aurora borealis, also known as the northern lights, may be visible in various regions of the United States this weekend. Due to a solar storm, the colorful celestial display could be witnessed across northern parts of the country, including Indiana, Missouri, Ohio, and Massachusetts. The optimal viewing times are predicted to be after midnight on Friday, September 30th, through the early hours of Saturday, October 1st. Skywatchers in Texas, Iowa, and Amarillo, Texas, are also encouraged to look towards the northern horizon for a chance to witness the rare spectacle. Experts advise that clear skies and avoidance of light pollution will enhance the visibility of the aurora borealis.
